        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 5:00PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 459 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Max, or 12
miles northeast of Garrison, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Max and Benedict.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
